description: Things That Caught My Attention is a newsletter about the internet and life that I’ve been writing since January 2014. I’ve been writing online since 1998. In other words, I wrote about anything that software touches. I don’t just write about technology: I also write about technology from a personal perspective. I write about adult ADHD, mental health, what it’s like to be a father and what it’s like to be an immigrant in America raising a family. Paid supporters and subscribers now get a free copy of Things That Caught My Attention, Volume 1, an ebook collecting the best essays from the first fifty episodes.
